                  <handDesc>
                     <!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, somewhat irregular</seg>
                        <seg type="script">The hand is characterized
                           by:  - the letter ለ has nearly vertical
                           right leg; - the letter ሥ presents a smaller
                           right loop; the letter ሣ has a smaller left
                           loop.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <date>18th century</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሰ፡/ ሰላ፡</abbr> for <expan>ሰላም፡ </expan> (Text I-1, Text I-4 –
                              Text I-14) .</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ጊ፡/ ጊዮ፡</abbr> for <expan>ጊዮርጊስ፡ </expan> (Text I-5, I-6)
                              .</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ፋሲሊዳ፡</abbr> for <expan>ፋሲሊደስ፡ </expan> (Text I-9).</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ገለው፡/ ገለውዴ፡</abbr> for <expan>ገለውዴዎስ፡ </expan> (Text
                              I-10).</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ዮሐን፡</abbr> for <expan>ዮሐንስ፡ </expan> (Text I-11, Text
                              I-12).</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; name of the donor (fol. 91vb);
                           incipits of Text I and its subsections (a few lines are rubricated,
                           alternating with black lines, on fols. 1ra-rb, 10va-vb); incipit of Text
                           II; the word säläm in Text I-1 and from Text I-4 up to Text I-14; the
                           word ʾO-za-...and the following verbal form in Text I-2; the word
                           tämaḫǝḍänku in Text I-3; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of
                           Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#85vb">f. 85vb l.1</locus>
                           <desc>Ownership note. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘቄስ፡
                              ተስፋ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ሣምራ፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ውጉዝ፡ ይኩን።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">
                              This book is of priest Tasfā
                              Śǝllāse (of) Śamra. The one who stole it or the one who scratched
                              (what is written in it), shall be excommunicated. </q>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2"> <locus target="#93rb">f. 93rb l.7</locus>
                           <desc> ʾAsmat-prayer.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                               በስመ፡ አብ፡ በል፡ ከል፡ ተከልከል ፯ጊዜ፡
                              ሔጄርጄ፡ ፯ጊዜ፡ ጉሐጄን፡ ወጉበርጄን፯ጊዜ፡…</q>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1"><desc> The title of Text I is crudely written on the front
                           leather cover with yellow paint.&#xD; - Titles of the works (<locus target="#8r">8r</locus> መልክአ፡ ማርያም፡ Malkǝʾa Māryām, <locus target="#9r">9r</locus> (መልክአ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ Malkǝʾa ʾIyasus) are crudely
                           written in blue pen in the upper margins.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><desc>Short ownership note
                           (ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘማይ፡ አንበሳ፡) is crudely written in a recent hand, below Additio 1:
                           <locus target="#85vb">85vb</locus>.</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"><desc>Note, correction (?)
